    "Historian of Italian Renaissance art, particularly of religious iconography.": [],
    "Born Evelyn May Graham Sandberg, she was born in 1888 to Reverend George Alfred Sandberg (1848~1910), a Clerk of the Holy Orders; her mother, Annie (1858-1894), died when she was six.": [],
    "She studied geography and geomorphology at the Society of Oxford Home-Students\u2014 now St.": [],
    "Anne\u2019s College\u2014 before teaching geography at a girls\u2019 grammar school starting in 1912.": [],
    "She then married climatologist Wilfrid Kendrew (1884-1962), who was likely her teacher prior, with whom she had one son, John Kendrew (1917-1997).": [
