    "Her first major publication was <em>La pittura veronese del trecento e del primo quattrocento</em>, 1926, which focused on so-called primitive art from Verona and has been described as a pioneer text for the topic.": [],
    "Under the advice of Berenson, her next work, 1929\u2019s <em>La croce dipinta italiana</em>, centered on the study of Italian painted crosses and was called \u201cher most important work\u201d by her friend and important British art historian, <a href=\"/popehennessyj\">John Pope-Hennessy</a> (1919-1994), who hailed it \u201cas in the literal sense, [a] definitive\u201d exploration of the topic.": [
        [
